President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate several individuals for key roles in his administration. These include Amanda Bennett for Chief Executive Officer at the United States Agency for Global Media, Jose Emilio Esteban for Under Secretary for Food Safety at the United States Department of Agriculture, Geeta Rao Gupta for Ambassador at Large for Global Women's Issues at the U.S. Department of State, Glenna Gallo for Assistant Secretary for Special Education and Rehabilitative Services at the Department of Education, Christopher Lowman for Assistant Secretary of Defense for Sustainment at the Department of Defense, Erin McKee for Assistant Administrator for Europe and Eurasia at the United States Agency for International Development, and Christopher J. Williamson for Assistant Secretary for Mine Safety and Health at the Department of Labor. These individuals have extensive experience and qualifications in their respective fields.